Bluetongue, Brazil
------------------
Information received on [and dated] 22 Jul 2016 from Dr Guilherme Henrique Figueiredo Marques, director, [Animal Health Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Food Supply of Brazil], Brasilia, Brazil

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 10 Apr 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 15 Jul 2016
Date event resolved: 20 Jul 2016
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: bluetongue virus
Serotype: 19
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Foz do Iguacu, Parana
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Apr 2016
Outbreak status: resolved 20 Jul 2016
Epidemiological unit: zoo
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Pygmy brocket: _Mazama nana_ (Cervidae) / 29 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Deer from the indigenous fauna (_Mazama nana_), 2 years old, held in captivity in a zoo within the ecological reserve of the Itaipu Binacional dam. The animal, which presented clinical signs and pathological injuries suitable with bluetongue, died 3 days after the start of the clinical disease.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Pygmy brocket: _Mazama nana_ (Cervidae) / 3.45 / 3.45 / 100 / 3.45
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Phylogenetic analysis of the sample by the Animal virology investigation Laboratory of the Minas Gerais Federal University identified serotype 19. A bluetongue outbreak already occurred in the same area last year [2015], but with different serotypes.

Control measures
Measures applied: vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type/ Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal virology investigation Laboratory of the Minas Gerais Federal University (Local laboratory)/ Pygmy brocket / real-time reverse transcriptase / polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 15 Jul 2016 / Positive
Animal virology investigation Laboratory of the Minas Gerais Federal University (Local laboratory)/ Pygmy brocket / serotyping / 15 Jul 2016 / Positive
Animal virology investigation Laboratory of the Minas Gerais Federal University (Local laboratory)/ Pygmy brocket / virus isolation / 15 Jul 2016 / Positive
Animal virology investigation Laboratory of the Minas Gerais Federal University (Local laboratory)/ Pygmy brocket / virus sequencing / 15 Jul 2016 / Positive
Lanagro (national laboratory)/ Pygmy brocket / real-time reverse transcriptase / polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 29 Apr 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

